      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "hey i just finished changing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i pull into my driveway i hear this really high pitched squealing sound coming from the front end. not sure if i messed something up or if it means the sensor is bad or something? any idea if its the caliper or just the pads settling?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Squeeee-y! That high-pitched whine sounds almost as obnoxious as a clutch of goblins trying to steal shiny things right out of your chimney. Changing brake pads, especially, can sometimes cause these high-pitched noises; it could be that the new pads aren't seated perfectly or the caliper is a bit misaligned. You might need to lightly bed-in the new pads by doing some moderate stops from a moderate speed, which iron-wills can sometimes manage before they complain! If bedding them in doesn't stop the squealing, then the caliper itself might be the issue. G",
